[30;1m42 | [0m[35mUsing crypto in your application [shouldn't have to][devs_are_users_too_slides][0m
[30;1m43 | [0m[35mfeel like juggling chainsaws in the dark. Tink is a crypto library written by a[0m
[30;1m44 | [0m[35mgroup of cryptographers and security engineers at Google. It was born out of our[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35mextensive experience working with Google's product teams,[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35m[fixing weaknesses in implementations](https://github.com/google/wycheproof),[0m

[30;1m82 | [0m[35m    Raises:[0m
[30;1m83 | [0m[35m      TinkError if there was a permanent error.[0m

[30;1m36 | [0m[35m  modular construction of compound primitives from 'simple' ones,[0m
[30;1m37 | [0m[35m  e.g., AES-CTR-HMAC AEAD encryption uses IND-CPA encryption and a MAC.[0m
[30;1m38 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m40 | [0m[35m  primitives for given keys or keysets.[0m
